- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with computability and complexity of functions over the reals, which is a topic that falls under numerical analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a notion of computability and complexity for real functions, which can be seen as a new algorithmic framework for analyzing such functions. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper may involve some logical reasoning in developing the notion of computability and complexity for real functions. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper may involve some symbolic manipulation of real functions in order to analyze their complexity.
